the rsa cryptosystem is based on this theorem it implies that the inverse of the function formula where formula is the public encryption exponent is the function formula where formula the private decryption exponent is the multiplicative inverse of formula modulo formula the difficulty of computing formula without knowing the factorization of formula is thus the difficulty of computing formula this is known as the rsa problem which can be solved by factoring formula the owner of the private key knows the factorization since an rsa private key is constructed by choosing formula as the product of two randomly chosen large primes formula and formula only formula is publicly disclosed and given the difficulty to factor large numbers we have the guarantee that no one else knows the factorization
