totient numbers
a totient number is a value of euler's totient function that is an m for which there is at least one x for which x m the valency or multiplicity of a totient number m is the number of solutions to this equation a nontotient is a natural number which is not a totient number there are infinitely many nontotients and indeed every odd number has an even multiple which is a nontotient
the number of totient numbers up to a given limit x is
