transcendental humanism

transcendental humanism in philosophy considers what is proper treatment of humans outside of nature and decides they have inherent rights simply from being human it is also positive that man is capable of transcending the material self and can also free himself from surrounding influences an example of this is when he thinks about himself and his character traits as if two different people kant by the term meant humans are both a part of creation and able to transcend reflexive obedience to the laws of nature in clinical psychology transcendental humanism is the principle that people are more important than their circumstances and that people have know this from their common sense rather than from the ancient greek pantheon or from god or from some other culture's religious traditions and claims about truth are rationally based on and checked by actual experiences
characteristics of experience
